    "chapter": {
        "bookTitle": "1 John",
        "delineation": "Chapter",
        "number": 4,
        "summary": "Try the spirits\u2014God is love and dwells in those who love Him.",
        "chapterAugmentations": [],
        "verses": [
            {
                "text": "Beloved, believe not every spirit, but try the spirits whether they are of God: because many false prophets are gone out into the world.",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "Moro. 7:12 (12\u201317).",
                        "start": 27,
                        "end": 33
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "GR\u00a0test, prove by trial, discern. 1\u00a0Thes. 5:21; D&C 11:12 (12\u201314); 50:31 (1\u20133, 31\u201335); 129:9 (1\u20139).",
                        "start": 39,
                        "end": 42
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "TG\u00a0Spirits, Evil or Unclean.",
                        "start": 47,
                        "end": 54
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "TG\u00a0Apostasy of the Early Christian Church; False Prophets.",
                        "start": 93,
                        "end": 107
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": []
            },
            {
                "text": "Hereby know ye the Spirit of God: Every spirit that confesseth that Jesus Christ is come in the flesh is of God:",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "TG\u00a0Discernment, Spiritual.",
                        "start": 7,
                        "end": 11
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "TG\u00a0God, Spirit of.",
                        "start": 19,
                        "end": 25
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "TG\u00a0Flesh and Blood.",
                        "start": 96,
                        "end": 101
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": []
            },
            {
                "text": "And every spirit that confesseth not that Jesus Christ is come in the flesh is not of God: and this is that spirit of antichrist, whereof ye have heard that it should come; and even now already is it in the world.",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "D&C 50:32.",
                        "start": 79,
                        "end": 89
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "TG\u00a0Antichrist.",
                        "start": 118,
                        "end": 128
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": [
                    {
                        "start": 108,
                        "end": 114
                    }
                ]
            },
            {
                "text": "Ye are of God, little children, and have overcome them: because greater is he that is in you, than he that is in the world.",
                "footnotes": [],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": []
            },
            {
                "text": "They are of the world: therefore speak they of the world, and the world heareth them.",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "TG\u00a0Worldliness.",
                        "start": 16,
                        "end": 21
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": []
            },
            {
                "text": "We are of God: he that knoweth God heareth us; he that is not of God heareth not us. Hereby know we the spirit of truth, and the spirit of error.",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "John 8:47; 13:20; D&C 1:38 (14, 37\u201338); 29:7; 84:36 (35\u201339).",
                        "start": 35,
                        "end": 42
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "TG\u00a0Discernment, Spiritual.",
                        "start": 92,
                        "end": 96
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "TG\u00a0Holy Ghost, Mission of.",
                        "start": 104,
                        "end": 110
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "GR\u00a0deception, wandering, sin.",
                        "start": 139,
                        "end": 144
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": []
            },
            {
                "text": "Beloved, let us love one another: for love is of God; and every one that loveth is born of God, and knoweth God.",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "TG\u00a0Love.",
                        "start": 16,
                        "end": 20
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "TG\u00a0God, Love of.",
                        "start": 38,
                        "end": 42
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "TG\u00a0Man, New, Spiritually Reborn.",
                        "start": 83,
                        "end": 94
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": []
            },
            {
                "text": "He that loveth not knoweth not God; for God is love.",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "John 17:3.",
                        "start": 19,
                        "end": 26
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": []
            },
            {
                "text": "In this was manifested the love of God toward us, because that God sent his only begotten Son into the world, that we might live through him.",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "John 3:16.",
                        "start": 124,
                        "end": 128
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": []
            },
            {
                "text": "Herein is love, not that we loved God, but that he loved us, and sent his Son to be the propitiation for our sins.",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "2\u00a0Thes. 2:16.",
                        "start": 51,
                        "end": 56
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "TG\u00a0Jesus Christ, Authority of.",
                        "start": 65,
                        "end": 69
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "TG\u00a0Jesus Christ, Atonement through; Jesus Christ, Redeemer.",
                        "start": 88,
                        "end": 100
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": [
                    {
                        "start": 78,
                        "end": 83
                    }
                ]
            },
            {
                "text": "Beloved, if God so loved us, we ought also to love one another.",
                "footnotes": [],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": []
            },
            {
                "text": "No man hath seen God at any time. If we love one another, God dwelleth in us, and his love is perfected in us.",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "JST\u00a01\u00a0Jn. 4:12 No man hath seen God at any time, except them who believe\u00a0\u2026",
                        "start": 0,
                        "end": 2
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "D&C 93:1; 110:2 (1\u20133); Abr. 3:11 (11\u201312); JS\u2014H 1:17 (16\u201317).",
                        "start": 12,
                        "end": 16
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "2\u00a0Cor. 13:5.",
                        "start": 58,
                        "end": 61
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "1\u00a0Cor. 2:16.",
                        "start": 62,
                        "end": 70
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [
                    {
                        "type": "paper-page-number",
                        "data": 1560
                    }
                ],
                "italics": []
            },
            {
                "text": "Hereby know we that we dwell in him, and he in us, because he hath given us of his Spirit.",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "1\u00a0Jn. 3:24.",
                        "start": 23,
                        "end": 28
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": []
            },
            {
                "text": "And we have seen and do testify that the Father sent the Son to be the Saviour of the world.",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "TG\u00a0Witness.",
                        "start": 24,
                        "end": 31
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "TG\u00a0Jesus Christ, Authority of.",
                        "start": 48,
                        "end": 52
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "TG\u00a0Jesus Christ, Savior.",
                        "start": 71,
                        "end": 78
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "D&C 66:1.",
                        "start": 86,
                        "end": 91
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": [
                    {
                        "start": 61,
                        "end": 66
                    }
                ]
            },
            {
                "text": "Whosoever shall confess that Jesus is the Son of God, God dwelleth in him, and he in God.",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "TG\u00a0Testimony.",
                        "start": 16,
                        "end": 23
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": []
            },
            {
                "text": "And we have known and believed the love that God hath to us. God is love; and he that dwelleth in love dwelleth in God, and God in him.",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "D&C 42:45.",
                        "start": 86,
                        "end": 94
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": []
            },
            {
                "text": "Herein is our love made perfect, that we may have boldness in the day of judgment: because as he is, so are we in this world.",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "TG\u00a0Jesus Christ, Exemplar.",
                        "start": 97,
                        "end": 99
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": []
            },
            {
                "text": "There is no fear in love; but perfect love casteth out fear: because fear hath torment. He that feareth is not made perfect in love.",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "Philip. 1:14 (12\u201317); D&C 50:41 (41, 42). TG\u00a0Courage; Fearful.",
                        "start": 12,
                        "end": 16
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "TG\u00a0Family, Love within.",
                        "start": 20,
                        "end": 24
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "TG\u00a0Love.",
                        "start": 38,
                        "end": 42
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "GR\u00a0correction, punishment.",
                        "start": 79,
                        "end": 86
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": []
            },
            {
                "text": "We love him, because he first loved us.",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "TG\u00a0Love.",
                        "start": 3,
                        "end": 7
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": []
            },
            {
                "text": "If a man say, I love God, and hateth his brother, he is a liar: for he that loveth not his brother whom he hath seen, how can he love God whom he hath not seen?",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "TG\u00a0Family, Love within; Hate.",
                        "start": 30,
                        "end": 36
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "TG\u00a0Brotherhood and Sisterhood.",
                        "start": 41,
                        "end": 48
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "TG\u00a0Lying.",
                        "start": 58,
                        "end": 62
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "1\u00a0Jn. 3:17 (10\u201318).",
                        "start": 91,
                        "end": 98
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "TG\u00a0God, Privilege of Seeing.",
                        "start": 155,
                        "end": 159
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": []
            },
            {
                "text": "And this commandment have we from him, That he who loveth God love his brother also.",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "TG\u00a0Fellowshipping; Love.",
                        "start": 51,
                        "end": 57
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": []
            }
        ]
    }
}